post_text:
Good afternoon,

Due to the information we have received from our local health services it is important that Gates County Public Schools continues to look after the safety of our staff and students. Providing food to families in Gates County is a priority for us but we must take further precautions to keep everyone safe. Starting tomorrow, April 3rd our staff members will not be exiting the buses to deliver food at stops. All deliveries must be picked up at the bus. Please be prepared for deliveries by watching or listening for the bus. For safety reasons drivers will only make one attempt to deliver food. If you miss your delivery, food will continue be available for pick up at the schools.

We will continue to keep you updated with any changes that may be necessary in the near future.

post_text:
Good evening,

Gates County Public Schools will begin transporting meals through our transportation department on Thursday, March 19th for students who normally ride the bus. It will be one delivery per day with a breakfast & lunch combo along with elementary work packets for students who have not already picked them up.

The buses will be leaving the schools at approximately 8:30 am., however, the times of meal drop-offs will vary from their normal pick up time. Parents, if you have pets or animals at your home, please contain them until you have received your delivery.

Headstart meals will be delivered by Headstart Staff.

Meal pickup and elementary packets for car riders and pre-k students will be available at the schools from 11:00-1:00 Monday through Friday. Middle and high school work packets will be delivered on Monday, March 23, 2020.

This is a rapidly changing event and we will provide updates as quickly possible. Please continue to stay healthy and safe.

Good morning, the Gates County Red Barons has been entered into the "Wear it Like a Pro" contest put on by the Carolina Panthers. One school in each classification (1A, 2A, 3A, & 4A) will be selected to win 24 FREE Speed Flex Helmets. This is about a $10,000 dollar value.

We have received thousands of votes and are out performing the bigger schools. Yesterday we jumped from 5th to 3rd over night! The standings are below as well as the link to go vote. We still have a ways to go but I believe we can do it. Please get everyone one involved (students, family, community, etc.). It will take a village but it can be done! You may vote as many times as you want or are willing between now and October 15th. Thanks again and Go Barons!

https://www.panthers.com/fans/wearitlikeapro

Good evening,

Gates County Schools will be offering a school bus drivers training class on March 19, 20, 21, 2018 from 8:30am – 3:30pm. This is a free class with space limited to 24 candidates. There will be 2 differing locations for this class, please call for details.

To become a bus driver for Gates County Schools, you must meet the following requirements:

-Be at least 18 years old

-Have a valid NC driver’s license for a minimum of 6 months

-Pass a physical examination as required by State Law

-Pass qualifications as determined by NCDMV

-Complete the Bus Driver Training Class sponsored by Gates County Schools and the North Carolina Department of Motor Vehicles (NCDMV)

The Bus Driver Training Class consists of three (3) days of classroom training and three (3) days of road training at a later date.

For more information please contact the Gates County Schools Transportation Department at (252) 357-0606 or (252) 312-4041 cell

Good morning,

Gates County High needs your help!
The video, "Mutation Station!", produced by Gates County High School biology students Meagan Atkins, Erin Greene and Camryn Byrum was selected as a finalist in the Biogen Spark Video Contest! Beginning March 1st, you may vote for the video once per day for the entire month of March.

Please visit the following site:
https://spark.biogenfoundation.com/

Click on the video under High Schools in NC to view the video and click on the red vote button to vote for the video.

The video with the most votes will earn the students GoPro Video Cameras and the school up to $10,000! Please, help us bring this honor to GCHS. We are a small, rural agrarian community so we are going to need the help of our community, family and friends. This honor would make the purchase of STEM science equipment a reality for our students. Thank you for helping the Red Barons!

Good evening,

We are pleased to announce that there will be online registration for New and Returning students in Gates Co. Schools for the 2017-18 school year. Online Registration will replace the cumbersome amount of papers that would normally be given to students on the first day of school that parents have to fill out and send back. Parents are required to have a Snapcode, and it will be given out at Open House at the Elementary and Middle Schools. A letter with the information was sent in the schedules for students who attend the High School. This system will save parents a tremendous amount of time especially if you have more than one student in the system. If you have questions, please call the District Data Center located on the campus of Gates Co. High @ 357-1710 or 357-2057.

post_text:
Please join us for our countywide arts night on February 29 (right before we leap into March--which is ARTS in our Schools Month!)

Come enjoy our students from all five schools as they explore the theme emotions through the arts. Emotions "play a vital part" in creative expression in the arts and our students have enjoyed exploring the many different emotions that make up our world. Patrons of the arts and family members will enjoy performances from our musicians in the band program, our dancers from GCHS and Gatesville Elementary, the choral groups from TS Cooper and Buckland Elementary, and a variety of actors from our schools. Art work from GCHS and Central Middle School artists will also be showcased. We hope to see you there!

February 29, 2016
When: 7:00 p.m.
Where: GCHS Big Gym

No cost. Family members welcome.
For more information, contact your local arts teacher!

HAPPY NEW YEAR GATES COUNTY:

New Beginnings Day Care is hosting a 5k Run/Walk Fundraising Event called "Run Wild For A Child" on Saturday, January 9th, 2016 at Merchants Millpond State Park at 10:00 a.m. There will also be a 1 mile Kids Fun Run at 11:00 a.m. followed by an Awards Ceremony and Lunch.

You can register either online through the school system website (look on the right side of the main page), or you may pick up a registration form at the daycare inside of Gatesville Elementary.

5K Run/Walk Event is $25.00 before the day of the race and $30.00 the day of the race.

1 Mile Kids Fun Run is $10.00 (children ages 10 and under). Yes, adults may join their child for this.

Hope to see you there,
New Beginnings Day Care Center Staff and Families

post_text: Good afternoon, at approximately 12:15, there was a lockdown at the high school. There were some unidentified visitors on campus which caused concern for the safety of our students. Under the advisement of law enforcement, the school was put in lockdown until the whereabouts of all our students were known. After confirmation that our students were safe and the campus secure, the lockdown was lifted. This entire process took approximately 25-30 minutes. I would like to thank the faculty, staff, and students for their quick response to the lockdown and the community involvement. If you have any questions, please contact an administrator at Gates County High School.

post_text: During the week of September 28, 2015, elementary, middle, and home school students got to visit the Speedway to Healthy exhibit set up at the Community Center. This is a 1,200 square foot walkthrough exhibit representing the human body and it is a resource to fight childhood obesity. Speedway to Healthy is a project of 4-H Youth Development of the Cooperative Extension Program, a division of the School of Agriculture and Environmental Sciences at NC A&T State University.

post_text:
Message from Mr. Billy Winn, Gates County Emergency Management, 9/30/15:

As you all are aware we are in the cone of uncertainty for Hurricane Joaquin. Emergency Management is monitoring the event closely and participating in conference calls with state and federal agencies. No track has been nailed down yet therefore this will be a short turn around storm. Worst case scenario is we see Isabel type wind damage and Floyd type water. Least case scenario we will be extra wet with 10 inches predicted throughout. We do not have immediate sheltering plans or other emergency actions to put in place as of yet. I just want you to know that this event MAY interrupt your weekend plans. I will keep you updated as I know anything, as usual be leery of social media HYPE. Stay informed but don’t freak out.
